1
00:00:14,880 --> 00:00:18,400
MAN: Signora, your school offers
a chance for betterment, escape.

2
00:00:18,480 --> 00:00:19,760
My daughter...

3
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:27,200
...Isabella is 17 now,

4
00:00:27,280 --> 00:00:30,760
but what prospects are there
for the daughter of a boat-builder?

5
00:00:30,840 --> 00:00:33,480
There's no future for us.
No future but you.

6
00:00:35,040 --> 00:00:37,480
I am moved by your concern
for your daughter.

7
00:00:39,240 --> 00:00:41,400
I believe protecting the future
of one's own

8
00:00:41,480 --> 00:00:44,400
- is a sacred duty.
- Signora...

9
00:00:46,480 --> 00:00:47,960
...she is my world.

10
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:58,720
Then we will take your world.

11
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:02,600
FATHER: I knew it!

12
00:01:02,680 --> 00:01:05,360
- I knew it!
- (FATHER AND DAUGHTER LAUGH)

13
00:01:07,240 --> 00:01:09,400
Say goodbye to your daughter.

14
00:01:11,240 --> 00:01:14,640
- Now, signora?
- Why wait?

15
00:01:14,720 --> 00:01:16,840
Time ticks.

16
00:01:21,440 --> 00:01:23,960
Be brave, my girl. Make me proud.

17
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,600
Step into the light, my dear.

18
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:34,280
(DOOR OPENS)

19
00:01:34,360 --> 00:01:35,560
That's it.

20
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:39,200
(DOOR SLAMS SHUT)

21
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:47,360
What say you, Francesco?
Do you like her?

22
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:49,480
Oh, I do, Mother.

23
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:51,480
I do.

24
00:01:54,880 --> 00:01:57,120
Hey...!

25
00:01:58,280 --> 00:02:00,720
It's me! Hello!

26
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:02,760
How are you?

27
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:04,920
The reason for this call is because

28
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:08,360
I haven't told you for seven hours
that I love you, which is a scandal,

29
00:02:08,480 --> 00:02:12,360
and even if we weren't getting married
tomorrow, I'd ask you to marry me anyway.

30
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:14,600
Yes, I would,

31
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:16,560
because you are smashing!

32
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:18,560
(# DAVID ROSE: The Stripper)

33
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:20,600
Oh... Oh. Oh, blimey.

34
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:23,320
I've... I've... I-I-I've got to go.

35
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:24,800
I'll see you tomorrow.

36
00:02:24,880 --> 00:02:26,640
(CHEERING AND WHISTLING)

37
00:02:26,720 --> 00:02:30,120
ALL: Out! Out! Out!

38
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:35,120
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

39
00:02:39,680 --> 00:02:41,000
Rory!

40
00:02:41,080 --> 00:02:44,480
That's a relief. I thought
I'd burst out of the wrong cake...

41
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:46,600
again. That reminds me,

42
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:49,800
there's a girl outside in a bikini. Could
someone let her in and give her a jumper?

43
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:52,800
Lucy. Lovely girl.
(WHISPERS) Diabetic.

44
00:02:54,080 --> 00:02:56,360
Now, then. Rory.

45
00:02:57,440 --> 00:02:59,760
We need to talk about your fiancée.

46
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:04,640
She tried to kiss me.

47
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:06,760
(THEY ALL GASP)

48
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:11,480
Tell you what, though,
you're a lucky man - she's a great kisser.

49
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:13,640
(GLASS SMASHES)

50
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:24,520
Funny how you can say something
in your head and it sounds fine...

51
00:04:02,040 --> 00:04:06,200
Oh! The life out there, it dazzles.

52
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:10,280
I mean, it blinds you
to the things that are important.

53
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:12,800
I've seen it devour relationships
and plans...

54
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:17,600
It's meant to do that.

55
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:22,520
...because for one person
to have seen all that,

56
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:24,640
to taste the glory
and then go back,

57
00:04:24,720 --> 00:04:27,800
it will tear you apart.

58
00:04:27,880 --> 00:04:30,440
So...I'm sending you somewhere.

59
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:31,960
Together.

60
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:34,120
Whoa! What, like a date?

61
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:36,720
Anywhere you want, any time you want.

62
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:38,800
One condition - it has to be amazing.

63
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:41,480
The Moulin Rouge in 1890!
The first Olympic Games!

64
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:43,760
Think of it as a wedding present,
because, frankly,

65
00:04:43,840 --> 00:04:45,720
it's either this or tokens.

66
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,960
It's a lot to take in, isn't it?

67
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:50,600
Tiny box, huge room inside.
What's that about? Let me explain.

68
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:54,040
- It's another dimension.
- It's basically another dimen... What?

69
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:57,880
After Prisoner Zero, I've been reading up
on all the latest scientific theories -

70
00:04:57,960 --> 00:05:00,000
FTL travel, parallel universes.

71
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:03,680
I like the bit when someone says,
"It's bigger on the inside!”

72
00:05:03,760 --> 00:05:06,520
I always look forward to that.

73
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:11,200
So, this date. I'm kind of done
with running down corridors.

74
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:12,640
- What do you think, Rory?

75
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:16,160
THE DOCTOR:
How about somewhere...romantic?

76
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:18,120
(GOAT BLEATS)

77
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:22,760
(METALLIC THRUMMING)

78
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:27,760
Venice!

79
00:05:28,880 --> 00:05:30,720
Venezia!

80
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:33,160
La Serenissima!

81
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:36,040
Impossible city. Preposterous city!

82
00:05:36,120 --> 00:05:39,240
Founded by refugees
running from Attila the Hun.

83
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:43,200
It was just a collection of little
wooden huts in the middle of the marsh,

84
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:47,720
but became one of
the most powerful cities in the world.

85
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:52,760
Constantly being invaded,
constantly flooding...

86
00:05:52,840 --> 00:05:56,360
constantly...just beautiful!

87
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:58,960
Ah, you've got to love Venice.

88
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:03,200
And so many people did -
Byron, Napoleon, Casanova.

89
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:05,080
Ooh, that reminds me.

90
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:08,440
1580. That's all right.
Casanova doesn't get born for 145 years.

91
00:06:08,520 --> 00:06:10,920
Don't want to run into him.
I owe him a chicken.

92
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:13,440
You owe Casanova a chicken?

93
00:06:13,520 --> 00:06:16,560
- Long story. We had a bet.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

94
00:06:16,640 --> 00:06:18,560
Papers, if you please.

95
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:21,520
Proof of residency,
current bill of medical inspection.

96
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:23,440
There you go, fella.

97
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:27,400
All to your satisfaction,
I think you'll find.

98
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:29,680
I am so sorry, Your Holiness.

99
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:31,480
I didn't realise.

100
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:33,760
No worries.
You were just doing your job.

101
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:36,320
Sorry, what exactly ls your job?

102
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:39,800
Checking for aliens -
visitors from foreign lands

103
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:42,720
- what might bring the plague with them.
- Oh, that's nice(!)

104
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:45,160
See where you bring me? The plague!

105
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:46,920
Don't worry, Viscountess.

106
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:49,760
- Oh...
- No, we're under quarantine here.

107
00:06:49,880 --> 00:06:53,320
No-one comes in, no-one goes out,
and all because of the grace and wisdom

108
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:56,320
of our patron, Signora Rosanna Calvierri.

109
00:06:56,400 --> 00:07:00,320
How interesting.
I heard the plague died out years ago.

110
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:02,760
Not out there.

111
00:07:02,840 --> 00:07:05,760
No, Signora Calvierri has seen it
with her own eyes.

112
00:07:05,840 --> 00:07:08,040
Streets are piled high with bodies,
she said.

113
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:09,120
Did she, now?

114
00:07:12,880 --> 00:07:14,480
Oi!

115
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:16,480
According to this, I am your eunuch!

116
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:19,120
Oh, yeah, I'lUl explain later.

117
00:07:25,640 --> 00:07:28,320
Veils down, girls.

118
00:07:31,080 --> 00:07:33,160
(WOMAN WHISPERS) It's the Calvierri girls.

119
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:44,720
- What do you want?
- Where's my Isabella?

120
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:46,600
What are you doing?
Get away from her!

121
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:49,280
Isabella!

122
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:53,720
Isabella!

123
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:56,600
- Ah! It's me!
- (HISSING)

124
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:57,960
Argh!

125
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:01,640
Girls! Come along!

126
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:04,880
She's gone.

127
00:08:10,960 --> 00:08:12,360
Isabella! It's me!

128
00:08:12,440 --> 00:08:16,000
- What was that about?
- Isabella...

129
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:19,000
Oh...! I hate it when he does that!

130
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:26,600
Who were those girls?

131
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:29,720
I thought everyone knew

132
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:31,360
- about the Calvierri school.
- My first day here.

133
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:35,000
Parents do all sorts of things
to get their children into good schools.

134
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:38,000
They move house,
they change religion.

135
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:44,000
So why are you trying to get her out?

136
00:08:44,080 --> 00:08:46,040
Something happens in there.

137
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:49,200
Something magical, something evil.

138
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:51,680
My own daughter didn't recognise me.

139
00:08:51,760 --> 00:08:55,480
And the girl who pushed me away,
her face...

140
00:08:56,880 --> 00:08:58,640
...like an animal.

141
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:06,080
I think it's time
I met this Signora Calvierri.

142
00:09:08,880 --> 00:09:10,920
- (DOOR CLOSES)
- Mother?

143
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:13,920
Mummy's hydrating, Francesco.

144
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:17,680
And we never interrupt Mummy
when she's hydrating.

145
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:25,560
- We were accosted again.
- (SHE GASPS)

146
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:27,920
A man made a grab
for one of the girls.

147
00:09:29,920 --> 00:09:33,520
The longer we wait,
the greater the risk of discovery.

148
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:36,240
I mean, we've already converted
more than enough.

149
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:39,600
Surely it's time to introduce them
to my brothers.

150
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:41,920
I shall decide
when we have enough.

151
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:45,480
If it's more you want, let me take
the girls into the city tonight.

152
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:48,080
- We could.
- We follow the plan.

153
00:09:49,680 --> 00:09:51,720
Let them hammer on our door...

154
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:54,400
beg to be taken.

155
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,520
(BELL TOLLS)

156
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:07,080
And what have you been doing?

157
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:12,200
Well...running.

158
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:15,720
And fighting.
I've been scared.

159
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:18,080
- More scared than I thought was...
- Did you miss me?

160
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:20,600
I...

161
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:23,040
I knew I'd be coming back.

162
00:10:24,640 --> 00:10:27,080
He was right.
It blots out everything else.

163
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:29,920
Rory...this is our date.

164
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:32,240
Let's not do this, not now.

165
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:34,400
(FLUTTERING)

166
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:35,600
Ha!

167
00:10:35,680 --> 00:10:42,600
- We are in Venice and it is 1580.
- ( SHE LAUGHS)

168
00:10:42,680 --> 00:10:43,720
I know!

169
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:45,920
(THEY BOTH LAUGH)

170
00:10:51,520 --> 00:10:53,040
Flowers, signor?

171
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:12,560
- (PIERCING SCREAM)
- What was that?

172
00:11:21,400 --> 00:11:23,080
(HE HISSES)

173
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:26,960
RORY: She'll be OK.

174
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:29,840
Where are you...? Amy! Come back!

175
00:11:44,920 --> 00:11:48,000
You have my daughter. ...Isabella!

176
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:50,720
You're not coming in, stop there!
We've told you...

177
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:53,280
You have my daughter. ...Isabella!

178
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:56,120
- I demand you let me see my daughter.
- Move away!

179
00:11:56,200 --> 00:12:00,040
Isabella! It's me! It's your father.

180
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:02,120
- We will arrest you...
- Isabella!

181
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:03,720
GUARD: Move on.

182
00:12:17,880 --> 00:12:19,480
Hello, handsome.

183
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:24,920
(IN UNISON) Who are you?

184
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:44,280
How are you doing that?
I...am...loving it.

185
00:12:44,360 --> 00:12:46,720
You're like Houdini,
only five slightly scary girls,

186
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:49,480
and he was shorter...will be shorter.
I'm rambling.

187
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:53,680
(IN UNISON) I'll ask you again, signor.
Who are you?

188
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:56,360
Why don't you check this out?

189
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:02,760
Library card.
Of course, it's with... He's...

190
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:04,320
I need the spare.

191
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:08,560
Pale, creepy girls
who don't like sunlight

192
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:10,720
and can't be seen in...

193
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:15,840
Ha! Am I thinking
what I think I'm thinking?

194
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:17,920
But the city. Why shut down the city?

195
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:19,760
- Unless...
- (IN UNISON) Leave now, signor,

196
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:22,960
or we shall call for the steward...

197
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:24,640
...if you are lucky.

198
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:26,160
Ooh!

199
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:28,680
(HISSING)

200
00:13:30,280 --> 00:13:33,120
Tell me the whole plan.

201
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:35,880
(MUTTERING) One day that'll work.

202
00:13:35,960 --> 00:13:38,560
Listen, I would love to stay here.
This whole thing...

203
00:13:38,640 --> 00:13:42,000
I'm thrilled.
Oh, this is Christmas!

204
00:13:42,080 --> 00:13:43,800
(HISSING)

205
00:13:43,880 --> 00:13:46,840
- Doctor! We just saw a vampire!
- I just met some vampires!

206
00:13:46,920 --> 00:13:48,800
(BOTH BABBLE AT ONCE)

207
00:13:48,880 --> 00:13:51,440
- And creepy girls and everything.
- Vampires!

208
00:13:54,560 --> 00:13:57,000
- We think we just saw a vampire.
- Yeah, yeah, I know.

209
00:13:57,080 --> 00:13:58,960
- Amy was just telling me.
- Yeah!

210
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:02,400
- The Doctor actually went to their house.
- Oh. Right. Well...

211
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:04,880
OK, so...first we need
to get back in there somehow.

212
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:07,080
- What?! Back in where?
- AMY: How do we do that?

213
00:14:07,160 --> 00:14:09,160
Come and meet my new friend.

214
00:14:10,640 --> 00:14:13,640
FATHER: As you saw,
there's no clear way in.

215
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:15,840
The House of Calvierri is like a fortress.

216
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:19,320
But there's a tunnel underneath it,

217
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,880
with a ladder and shaft
that leads up into the house.

218
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:24,200
I tried to get in once myself,

219
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,600
- but I hit a trapdoor.
- You need someone on the inside.

220
00:14:26,720 --> 00:14:29,280
- No.
- You don't know what I was going to say!

221
00:14:29,360 --> 00:14:32,520
That we pretend you're an applicant
for the school to get you inside,

222
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:34,160
and tonight you come down

223
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:36,120
- and open the trapdoor to let us in.
- Oh.

224
00:14:36,240 --> 00:14:38,560
- So you do know what I was going to say.
- RORY: Are you insane?

225
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:41,280
- We don't have another option.
- He said no, Amy.

226
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:44,320
- Listen to him.
- FATHER: There ls another option.

227
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:50,160
I work at the Arsenale.

228
00:14:50,240 --> 00:14:52,200
- We build the warships for the navy.
- (SNIFFS)

229
00:14:52,280 --> 00:14:54,000
THE DOCTOR: Gunpowder.

230
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:57,160
Most people just nick stationery
from where they work.

231
00:14:57,240 --> 00:15:02,880
Look, I have a thing about guns
and huge quantities of explosive.

232
00:15:02,960 --> 00:15:06,760
What do you suggest, then? We wait
until they turn her into an animal?

233
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:12,760
I'll be there three, four hours tops.

234
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:19,400
No, no, no, no, no, no.
It can't keep happening like this.

235
00:15:19,480 --> 00:15:21,440
This is how they go.

236
00:15:23,520 --> 00:15:27,160
But I have to know. We go together.
Say you're my daughter.

237
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:30,720
- What?! Don't listen to him!
- Your daughter? You look about nine.

238
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:32,040
Brother, then.

239
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:33,720
Too weird. Fiancé.

240
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:36,960
I'm not having him run around
telling people Ae's your fiancé!

241
00:15:37,040 --> 00:15:39,160
No. No, you're right.

242
00:15:39,240 --> 00:15:40,880
- Thank you.
- [ mean,

243
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:43,320
they've already seen the Doctor.
You should do it.

244
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:48,000
- Me?
- Yeah! You can be my brother.

245
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:53,000
Why is him being your brother weird,
but with me, it's OK?

246
00:15:53,080 --> 00:15:55,080
Actually, I thought you

247
00:15:55,160 --> 00:15:57,120
- were her fiancé.
- Yeah, that's not helping.

248
00:15:57,200 --> 00:16:00,880
This whole thing is mental!
They're vampires, for God's sake!

249
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:02,400
We hope.

250
00:16:04,520 --> 00:16:06,480
So if they're not vampires...?

251
00:16:06,560 --> 00:16:09,160
Makes you wonder
what could be so bad

252
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:13,080
it doesn't actually mind
us thinking it's a vampire.

253
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:17,800
So, basically, both of our parents
are dead from getting the plague.

254
00:16:17,880 --> 00:16:21,160
I'm a gondola...driver...

255
00:16:21,240 --> 00:16:25,040
so...money's a bit tight...

256
00:16:26,200 --> 00:16:28,880
...So having my...sister

257
00:16:28,960 --> 00:16:34,080
go to your school for special people
would be brilliant.

258
00:16:35,680 --> 00:16:37,440
Cheers.

259
00:16:39,320 --> 00:16:41,880
- Have we met?
- I've just got one of those faces.

260
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:45,560
- I wasn't talking to you.
- She's got the same face...

261
00:16:45,640 --> 00:16:48,920
- which is because she's my sister!
- Carlo, explain yourself.

262
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,680
Why have you brought me this imbecile?

263
00:16:50,760 --> 00:16:53,640
Signora, they have references
from His Majesty the King of Sweden.

264
00:16:53,720 --> 00:16:55,360
What?

265
00:16:55,440 --> 00:16:56,680
Let me see.

266
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:08,200
Well, now I see
what got my steward so excited.

267
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:10,880
What say you, Francesco? Do you like her?

268
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:13,960
Oh, I do, Mother.

269
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:18,640
- I do.
- Then we'd be delighted to accept her.

270
00:17:18,720 --> 00:17:20,920
Say goodbye to your sister.

271
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:24,600
Um...um...er...

272
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:28,680
Tell Uncle...Doctor...
I'll see you both pretty soon, OK?

273
00:17:31,760 --> 00:17:32,920
I'll be fine.

274
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:36,560
A-Amy!

275
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:49,520
(BREATHY GIRLISH LAUGHTER)

276
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:59,240
CARLO: There are clothes on the bed.
Get changed and wait here.

277
00:18:00,640 --> 00:18:02,080
Blimey!

278
00:18:02,160 --> 00:18:04,640
This is private education, then?

279
00:18:11,120 --> 00:18:12,240
Hey. Hello.

280
00:18:12,320 --> 00:18:14,280
I'm Amy.

281
00:18:15,560 --> 00:18:17,560
What's your name?

282
00:18:17,640 --> 00:18:19,560
Isabella.

283
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:25,440
We're going to get you out of here,
but I need you to tell me what's going on.

284
00:18:25,520 --> 00:18:27,480
What is this place?
What are they doing?

285
00:18:27,560 --> 00:18:28,960
They, um...

286
00:18:29,040 --> 00:18:31,160
they come at night.

287
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:35,640
They gather around my bed
and they take me to a room...

288
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:39,440
with this green light
and a chair with...

289
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:44,280
- with straps, as if for a surgeon.
- What happens in there?

290
00:18:46,280 --> 00:18:47,520
I wake up here.

291
00:18:49,160 --> 00:18:53,120
And the sunlight burns my skin
like candle wax.

292
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:56,600
(BELL TOLLS)

293
00:19:09,840 --> 00:19:13,440
- She'll be fine.
- You can promise me that, can you?

294
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:23,720
(DISTANT CRIES)

295
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:32,960
(DISTANT SHRIEKS)

296
00:19:42,440 --> 00:19:44,240
We're here.

297
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:56,440
Right. OK, I'll go first.
If anything happens to me, go back...

298
00:19:56,520 --> 00:19:58,040
What happened?

299
00:19:58,120 --> 00:19:59,520
Between you and Amy?

300
00:20:01,120 --> 00:20:02,800
- You said she kissed you.
- Now?!

301
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:04,760
You want to do this now?/

302
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:07,760
I have a right to know.

303
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:09,920
I'm getting married in 430 years.

304
00:20:15,160 --> 00:20:17,640
(WIND HOWLS)

305
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:28,320
- (AMY SHRIEKS, GLASS BREAKS)
- She was frightened. 7was frightened,

306
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:31,960
but we survived, and the relief of it...
and so she kissed me.

307
00:20:33,520 --> 00:20:35,200
- And you kissed her back?
- No.

308
00:20:35,280 --> 00:20:36,880
I kissed her mouth.

309
00:20:36,960 --> 00:20:38,360
Funny(!)

310
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:41,840
Rory...Rory, she kissed me because
I was there. It would have been you.

311
00:20:41,920 --> 00:20:43,400
- It should have been you.
- Yeah.

312
00:20:43,440 --> 00:20:46,040
- It should have been me.
- Exactly. That's why I brought you here.

313
00:20:46,120 --> 00:20:47,560
(GUST OF WIND)

314
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:50,520
THE DOCTOR: (WHISPERING) Can we
go and see the vampires now, please?

315
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:53,520
- Control yourself, child.
- (AMY GASPS)

316
00:20:53,600 --> 00:20:57,240
- Get your hands off me!
- Psychic paper.

317
00:20:57,320 --> 00:20:59,840
Did you really think
that would work on me?

318
00:21:10,560 --> 00:21:12,280
- Push!
- I'm pushing!

319
00:21:15,680 --> 00:21:18,120
Come on. There we are.

320
00:21:19,680 --> 00:21:21,120
THE DOCTOR: (WHISPERS) Amy!

321
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:22,760
Where's Amy?

322
00:21:23,680 --> 00:21:25,120
Amy!

323
00:21:27,520 --> 00:21:31,600
- I can't see a thing.
- Just as well I brought this, then.

324
00:21:33,400 --> 00:21:35,560
Ultraviolet. Portable sunlight.

325
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:38,080
- Yours is bigger than mine.
- Let's not go there.

326
00:21:38,160 --> 00:21:42,360
Where are you from?
Did you fall through the chasm?

327
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:44,360
Mother, this is pointless.
Let's just start the process.

328
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:48,520
Hold your tongue, Francesco!
I need to know what this girl is doing

329
00:21:48,600 --> 00:21:52,240
in the world of savages
with psychic paper. Who are you with?

330
00:21:52,320 --> 00:21:54,640
I scarcely believe
your idiot brother sent you.

331
00:21:54,720 --> 00:21:59,120
And what are you doing in my school?

332
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:01,880
OK, I'll tell you.

333
00:22:01,960 --> 00:22:06,080
- I'm from Ofsted.
- (LAUGHS) Put her in the chair.

334
00:22:06,160 --> 00:22:07,280
No!

335
00:22:07,360 --> 00:22:09,560
Get your hands off me!

336
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:14,160
Oh, make sport of me, will you?
Tease me as if I were your dog?

337
00:22:14,240 --> 00:22:16,200
Well, this dog has a bite, girl.

338
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:19,800
(HISSES)

339
00:22:22,080 --> 00:22:23,840
Doctor... (SCREAMS)

340
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:29,800
If we cancel now, we'll lose the deposit
on the village hall, the salsa band...

341
00:22:29,880 --> 00:22:31,320
(SIGHS HOPELESSLY)

342
00:22:35,840 --> 00:22:37,760
(WHISPERS) What happened to them?

343
00:22:37,840 --> 00:22:39,880
They've had all the moisture
taken out of them.

344
00:22:54,400 --> 00:22:55,720
Mother...

345
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:59,200
when you drink from her,
may we share?

346
00:22:59,280 --> 00:23:01,240
I'm so thirsty.

347
00:23:02,880 --> 00:23:04,440
Of course, darling.

348
00:23:04,520 --> 00:23:06,200
That's what vampires do, right?

349
00:23:06,280 --> 00:23:08,880
They drink your blood
and replace it with their own.

350
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:10,000
Yeah, except these people

351
00:23:10,080 --> 00:23:13,200
haven't just had their blood taken,
but all the water in their bodies.

352
00:23:13,280 --> 00:23:14,840
Why did they die?

353
00:23:14,920 --> 00:23:17,000
Why aren't they like
the girls in the school?

354
00:23:19,320 --> 00:23:22,000
Maybe not everyone
survives the process.

355
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:30,880
You know what's dangerous about you?

356
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:33,120
It's not that you make people take risks.

357
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:35,360
It's that you make them
want to impress you.

358
00:23:37,200 --> 00:23:39,680
You make it
so they don't want to let you down.

359
00:23:41,800 --> 00:23:46,720
You have no idea how dangerous you make
people to themselves when you're around.

360
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:50,920
VOICES IN UNISON: Who are you?

361
00:23:55,320 --> 00:23:56,800
We should run. Run!

362
00:23:58,360 --> 00:24:00,880
ROSANNA: This is how it works.

363
00:24:02,040 --> 00:24:05,680
First, we drink you till you're dry.

364
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:10,960
Then...we fill you with our blood.

365
00:24:11,040 --> 00:24:14,520
It rages through you like a fire,

366
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:16,120
changing you,

367
00:24:16,200 --> 00:24:19,440
until one morning you awake

368
00:24:19,520 --> 00:24:22,480
and your humanity is a dream...

369
00:24:22,560 --> 00:24:24,040
now faded.

370
00:24:26,760 --> 00:24:29,400
Or you die. (HE CHUCKLES)

371
00:24:29,480 --> 00:24:32,360
- That can happen.
- AMY: And if I survive?

372
00:24:32,440 --> 00:24:38,040
Then there are 10,000 husbands
waiting for you in the water.

373
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:41,160
Yeah, sorry.

374
00:24:41,240 --> 00:24:43,240
I'm kind of engaged.

375
00:24:45,280 --> 00:24:47,040
(ELECTRONIC FIZZLING)

376
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:02,840
(CLATTERING)

377
00:25:02,920 --> 00:25:05,400
THE DOCTOR: Oh! Rory, come on!

378
00:25:05,480 --> 00:25:07,920
(SHE GASPS)

379
00:25:12,680 --> 00:25:14,560
Cab for Amy Pond?

380
00:25:17,880 --> 00:25:20,960
(AMY SCREAMS)
She bit me!

381
00:25:21,040 --> 00:25:24,240
This rescue plan -
not exactly watertight, is it?

382
00:25:24,320 --> 00:25:26,040
Ha-ha!

383
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:28,200
Rory!

384
00:25:28,280 --> 00:25:29,600
- Amy!
- Quickly, through here!

385
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:34,760
Seal the house.

386
00:25:34,840 --> 00:25:37,200
- They're not vampires!
- What?!

387
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:40,440
I saw them. I saw her.
They're not vampires. They're aliens!

388
00:25:40,520 --> 00:25:43,200
- (SHE LAUGHS)
- Classic!

389
00:25:43,280 --> 00:25:45,280
That's good news?
What is wrong with you people?!

390
00:25:45,360 --> 00:25:48,680
(AMY AND THE DOCTOR LAUGH)

391
00:25:48,760 --> 00:25:51,280
Come on, Rory, move!

392
00:25:51,360 --> 00:25:53,080
Ha-ha!

393
00:25:55,800 --> 00:25:58,440
Keep moving! Come on, guys.

394
00:26:02,440 --> 00:26:03,640
Quickly.

395
00:26:03,720 --> 00:26:06,040
Get out. Quick!

396
00:26:07,120 --> 00:26:08,920
Oh...

397
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:12,200
- (BELL TOLLS)
- Come on, run!

398
00:26:12,280 --> 00:26:13,960
I can't!

399
00:26:15,880 --> 00:26:18,600
(LOUD CRACKLING)

400
00:26:18,680 --> 00:26:19,680
Oh!

401
00:26:19,760 --> 00:26:22,160
(HE GROANS)

402
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:33,160
- Is he dead?
- No, he's breathing.

403
00:26:43,760 --> 00:26:47,120
And so, in memory of the children
lost to the silence,

404
00:26:47,200 --> 00:26:51,520
the traitor is delivered to the arms
of those she betrayed.

405
00:26:55,640 --> 00:26:57,600
Do you expect me to drown?

406
00:26:58,720 --> 00:27:00,680
I'm Venetian!

407
00:27:00,760 --> 00:27:02,280
I can swim!

408
00:27:02,360 --> 00:27:05,000
We can all swim!

409
00:27:12,920 --> 00:27:14,440
Something touched my leg.

410
00:27:19,840 --> 00:27:22,600
They're all around me!

411
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:25,880
They bite!

412
00:27:31,960 --> 00:27:33,680
Now leave us.

413
00:27:44,640 --> 00:27:46,600
Mother!

414
00:27:48,040 --> 00:27:50,000
Change your form...

415
00:27:50,080 --> 00:27:53,040
or my brothers will think
they are being fed twice today.

416
00:27:58,480 --> 00:28:00,400
Not long now.

417
00:28:00,480 --> 00:28:02,600
It's not long.

418
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:15,160
(WOLF WHISTLE)

419
00:28:15,240 --> 00:28:20,120
Long way from Saturnyne,
aren't you...Sister of the Water?

420
00:28:22,040 --> 00:28:24,480
No, let me guess.

421
00:28:24,560 --> 00:28:26,880
The owner of the psychic paper.

422
00:28:28,400 --> 00:28:30,520
Then I take it
you're a refugee, like me.

423
00:28:33,040 --> 00:28:35,800
I'll make you a deal.
An answer for an answer.

424
00:28:37,360 --> 00:28:40,520
You're using a perception filter.
It doesn't change your features,

425
00:28:40,600 --> 00:28:44,360
but manipulates the brainwaves
of the person looking at you.

426
00:28:44,440 --> 00:28:48,600
But seeing one of you
for the first time in, say, a mirror,

427
00:28:48,680 --> 00:28:53,520
the brain doesn't know what to fill
the gap with, so leaves it blank...

428
00:28:54,880 --> 00:28:57,080
...hence no reflection.

429
00:28:57,160 --> 00:28:58,480
Your question?

430
00:28:58,560 --> 00:29:01,000
Why can we see your big teeth?

431
00:29:01,080 --> 00:29:02,920
Self-preservation overrides the mirage.

432
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:06,920
The subconscious perceives the threat
and tries to alert the conscious brain.

433
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:08,800
- Where's Isabella?
- My turn.

434
00:29:10,720 --> 00:29:13,080
Where are you from?

435
00:29:13,160 --> 00:29:16,720
- Gallifrey.
- You should be in a museum.

436
00:29:16,800 --> 00:29:20,440
- Or in a mausoleum.
- Why are you here?

437
00:29:21,680 --> 00:29:24,240
We ran from the silence.

438
00:29:24,320 --> 00:29:28,360
- Why are you here?
- Wedding present. The silence?

439
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:32,640
There were cracks.

440
00:29:34,360 --> 00:29:35,920
Some were tiny...

441
00:29:38,240 --> 00:29:40,360
...some were as big as the sky.

442
00:29:42,360 --> 00:29:45,000
Through some we saw worlds and people

443
00:29:45,080 --> 00:29:47,960
and through others we saw silence...

444
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:52,080
...and the end of all things.

445
00:29:53,640 --> 00:29:59,160
We fled to an ocean like ours
and the crack snapped shut behind us...

446
00:30:00,720 --> 00:30:03,000
...and Saturnyne was lost.

447
00:30:04,920 --> 00:30:07,120
So Earth is to become
Saturnyne Mark II?

448
00:30:07,200 --> 00:30:09,240
And you can help me.

449
00:30:10,880 --> 00:30:14,040
We can build a new society here,
as others have.

450
00:30:16,520 --> 00:30:18,720
What do you say?

451
00:30:18,800 --> 00:30:20,040
Hmm.

452
00:30:31,080 --> 00:30:33,320
Where's Isabella?

453
00:30:34,440 --> 00:30:37,280
- Isabella?
- The girl who saved my friend.

454
00:30:38,880 --> 00:30:40,800
Oh, deserters must be executed.

455
00:30:40,880 --> 00:30:42,880
Any general will tell you that.

456
00:30:42,960 --> 00:30:44,600
I need an answer, Doctor.

457
00:30:44,680 --> 00:30:46,640
A partnership.

458
00:30:49,600 --> 00:30:51,560
Any which way you choose.

459
00:30:51,640 --> 00:30:54,120
I don't think that's
such a good idea, do you?

460
00:30:54,200 --> 00:30:57,040
I'm a Time Lord.

461
00:30:57,120 --> 00:30:59,040
You're a big fish.

462
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:03,680
Think of the children.

463
00:31:04,800 --> 00:31:06,320
Carlo!

464
00:31:06,400 --> 00:31:07,480
You're right.

465
00:31:07,560 --> 00:31:09,520
We're nothing alike.

466
00:31:09,600 --> 00:31:12,000
I will bend the heavens to save my race,

467
00:31:12,080 --> 00:31:15,440
- while you philosophise.
- This ends today.

468
00:31:15,520 --> 00:31:20,360
I will tear down the House of Calvierri,
stone by stone.

469
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:23,760
Take your hands off me, Carlo.

470
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:28,840
And you know why?

471
00:31:30,200 --> 00:31:32,840
You didn't know Isabella's name.

472
00:31:32,920 --> 00:31:34,840
(DOOR OPENS)

473
00:31:34,920 --> 00:31:37,400
You didn't know Isabella's name.

474
00:31:44,040 --> 00:31:45,320
CARLO: Open the gates.

475
00:31:51,800 --> 00:31:53,400
Attend!

476
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:57,560
Attend!

477
00:31:58,640 --> 00:32:01,560
The storm is coming!

478
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:08,880
- Argh!
- Mummy...

479
00:32:11,160 --> 00:32:13,440
What's wrong with
your perception filter?

480
00:32:13,520 --> 00:32:16,560
That idiot child must have damaged it
when she kicked me...

481
00:32:25,600 --> 00:32:27,400
(SHE PANTS)

482
00:32:27,480 --> 00:32:30,880
Now...assemble the girls.

483
00:32:30,960 --> 00:32:33,320
I have a job for them.

484
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:37,760
(ELECTRONIC WHIRRING)

485
00:32:39,240 --> 00:32:40,640
You're fine.

486
00:32:42,080 --> 00:32:43,360
Open wide.

487
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:46,680
- Mm-mm.
- Mm-mm.

488
00:32:46,760 --> 00:32:49,080
THE DOCTOR: Argh!

489
00:32:49,160 --> 00:32:52,880
I need to think.
Come on brain, think, think. Think!

490
00:32:52,960 --> 00:32:53,920
Think!

491
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:56,320
If they're fish people,
it explains why they hate the sun.

492
00:32:56,400 --> 00:32:58,600
Stop talking, brain thinking. Hush.

493
00:32:58,680 --> 00:33:00,920
- It's the school I don't understand.
- Stop talking, brain thinking. Hush.

494
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:02,560
I say we take the fight to them.

495
00:33:02,640 --> 00:33:03,960
- Ah-ah-ah!
- What?

496
00:33:04,040 --> 00:33:05,760
Ah!

497
00:33:05,840 --> 00:33:09,480
Her planet dies, so they flee
through a crack in space and time,

498
00:33:09,560 --> 00:33:12,360
and end up here, then she closes off
the city and, one by one,

499
00:33:12,480 --> 00:33:15,000
changes the people into creatures like her
to start a new gene pool.

500
00:33:15,120 --> 00:33:18,640
Got it. Then what? They come from the sea,
they can't survive for ever on land,

501
00:33:18,720 --> 00:33:21,600
so what's she going to do?

502
00:33:23,280 --> 00:33:25,480
Unless she's going to do something
to the environment

503
00:33:25,560 --> 00:33:28,480
to make the city habitable...

504
00:33:28,560 --> 00:33:31,360
She said, "I shall bend the heavens
to save my race.”

505
00:33:31,440 --> 00:33:33,040
Bend the heavens...

506
00:33:33,120 --> 00:33:37,120
Bend...the heavens...

507
00:33:37,200 --> 00:33:41,920
- She's going to sink Venice.
- She's...she's going to sink Venice?

508
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:45,160
And repopulate it
with the girls she's transformed.

509
00:33:45,240 --> 00:33:49,640
You can't repopulate somewhere
with just women.

510
00:33:49,720 --> 00:33:51,560
You need...blokes.

511
00:33:51,640 --> 00:33:53,360
- She's got blokes.
- Where?

512
00:33:53,480 --> 00:33:57,000
In the canal. She said, "There are
10,000 husbands waiting in the water."”

513
00:33:57,080 --> 00:33:59,360
Only the male offspring
survived the journey here.

514
00:33:59,440 --> 00:34:01,960
She's got 10,000 children
swimming around the canals,

515
00:34:02,040 --> 00:34:04,880
waiting for Mum to make them
some compatible girlfriends.

516
00:34:04,960 --> 00:34:06,360
Eugh!

517
00:34:06,440 --> 00:34:09,480
I mean, I've been around a bit,
but, really, that's...

518
00:34:09,560 --> 00:34:12,080
that's... Eugh!

519
00:34:12,160 --> 00:34:14,360
(CLATTERING)

520
00:34:16,160 --> 00:34:18,200
The people upstairs are very noisy.

521
00:34:18,280 --> 00:34:22,000
- There aren't any people upstairs.
- I knew you were going to say that.

522
00:34:22,080 --> 00:34:24,840
Did anyone else know
he was going to say that?

523
00:34:24,920 --> 00:34:26,360
(CREAKING)

524
00:34:26,440 --> 00:34:28,160
(WHISPERS) Is it the vampires?

525
00:34:28,240 --> 00:34:30,920
Like I said, they're not vampires.

526
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:33,320
Fish from space.

527
00:34:33,400 --> 00:34:36,160
(THUMP, GLASS BREAKS)

528
00:34:42,320 --> 00:34:44,280
Aren't we on the second floor?

529
00:34:53,960 --> 00:34:55,760
(ELECTRONIC WHIRRING)

530
00:34:55,840 --> 00:34:58,000
GUIDO: What's happened to them?

531
00:34:58,080 --> 00:35:01,120
There's nothing left of them.
They've been fully converted.

532
00:35:01,200 --> 00:35:03,680
Blimey, fish from space
have never been so...

533
00:35:04,720 --> 00:35:06,400
...buxom.

534
00:35:06,480 --> 00:35:07,800
OK...

535
00:35:07,880 --> 00:35:10,080
Move. Come on.

536
00:35:14,880 --> 00:35:17,280
Give me the lamp.

537
00:35:17,360 --> 00:35:20,200
Go, go, go, guys!
Keep moving, go, go go!

538
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:25,920
- Stay away from the door, Doctor.
- No! Guido! What are you doing?!

539
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:29,520
I'm not leaving you.
What are you doing?!

540
00:35:31,280 --> 00:35:33,160
- (ELECTRONIC WHIRRING)
- Bolted!

541
00:35:34,280 --> 00:35:35,800
Come on. That's it...

542
00:35:37,160 --> 00:35:38,320
Come on.

543
00:35:38,400 --> 00:35:39,640
Guido!

544
00:35:39,720 --> 00:35:41,000
(BIRD FLUTTERS)

545
00:35:41,080 --> 00:35:43,480
(GUIDO CHUCKLES)

546
00:35:43,560 --> 00:35:44,600
Come on.

547
00:35:44,680 --> 00:35:46,880
Come on. Come on!

548
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:55,600
We are Venetians!

549
00:36:08,080 --> 00:36:13,640
Right, to begin,
let's fill the sky with fire.

550
00:36:27,120 --> 00:36:28,480
Yes!

551
00:36:28,560 --> 00:36:31,720
MAN: In sight of the Lord,
protect and keep us!

552
00:36:40,080 --> 00:36:44,640
- Rosanna's initiating the final phase.
- We need to stop her. Come on!

553
00:36:44,720 --> 00:36:46,920
No, no. Get back to the TARDIS.

554
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:48,960
- You can't stop her on your own.
- We don't discuss this!

555
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:52,200
7 tell you to do something, Amy,
and yow do it.

556
00:36:53,320 --> 00:36:54,520
Huh?

557
00:36:56,440 --> 00:36:58,080
Thank you.

558
00:37:00,320 --> 00:37:01,280
Yeah...

559
00:37:01,360 --> 00:37:03,320
you're welcome.

560
00:37:03,400 --> 00:37:06,960
(SCREAMING)

561
00:37:15,840 --> 00:37:17,760
AMY: Oh, my God! What is going on?

562
00:37:17,840 --> 00:37:20,800
RORY: The sky, it's like it's boiling.

563
00:37:40,200 --> 00:37:42,360
(ELECTRONIC WHIRRING)

564
00:37:42,440 --> 00:37:45,000
You're too late.

565
00:37:45,080 --> 00:37:47,240
Such determination...

566
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:50,920
...just to save one city.

567
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:52,920
Hard to believe it's the same man

568
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:55,960
that let an entire race
turn to cinders and ash.

569
00:37:56,040 --> 00:38:01,440
Now you can watch
as my people take their new kingdom.

570
00:38:01,520 --> 00:38:03,000
The girls have gone, Rosanna.

571
00:38:05,560 --> 00:38:07,040
You're lying.

572
00:38:07,120 --> 00:38:08,800
Shouldn't I be dead?

573
00:38:10,320 --> 00:38:11,720
Hmm?

574
00:38:12,960 --> 00:38:18,000
Rosanna, please, help me.
There are 200,000 people in this city.

575
00:38:18,080 --> 00:38:19,520
So save them.

576
00:38:19,600 --> 00:38:22,120
(BEEPING)

577
00:38:24,320 --> 00:38:26,320
(CRASH!)

578
00:38:27,800 --> 00:38:30,320
(LIGHTNING CRACKS)

579
00:38:37,560 --> 00:38:40,160
Amy, run!

580
00:38:43,920 --> 00:38:46,600
This way, you freak! No! This.. this...

581
00:38:46,680 --> 00:38:49,640
this way, you big, stupid,
great...SpongeBob!

582
00:38:49,720 --> 00:38:53,080
The only thing I've seen
uglier than you is...your mum!

583
00:38:53,160 --> 00:38:54,800
Huh?

584
00:38:58,640 --> 00:39:00,640
No...

585
00:39:00,720 --> 00:39:03,600
Did you just say
something about Mummy?

586
00:39:05,720 --> 00:39:07,120
Ha! Ha!

587
00:39:09,200 --> 00:39:10,760
Ssh...

588
00:39:10,840 --> 00:39:12,800
Shoo...ssh...

589
00:39:12,880 --> 00:39:14,920
Argh!

590
00:39:19,080 --> 00:39:20,320
Ah...

591
00:39:21,400 --> 00:39:24,240
(HE CHUCKLES)

592
00:39:29,280 --> 00:39:30,760
AMY: Careful!

593
00:39:35,960 --> 00:39:37,880
- Hit him!
- Argh...

594
00:39:37,960 --> 00:39:40,320
(RORY GRUNTS)

595
00:39:40,400 --> 00:39:43,120
This way, bring him this way! Rory!

596
00:39:53,360 --> 00:39:54,880
Oh, you stink of fish!

597
00:39:56,200 --> 00:39:58,960
Well, I'm hardly going to smell
of cheese and biscuits(!)

598
00:40:01,640 --> 00:40:03,640
Oow!

599
00:40:07,560 --> 00:40:09,880
Hey! Mummy's boy.

600
00:40:19,480 --> 00:40:21,080
Ohh...

601
00:40:21,160 --> 00:40:22,720
- Oh...
- That was lucky.

602
00:40:22,800 --> 00:40:24,960
(CHICKENS CLUCK)

603
00:40:25,040 --> 00:40:28,240
Why did you make the sign of a cross,
you numpty?

604
00:40:28,320 --> 00:40:32,240
Oh, oh, right!
I'm being reviewed now, am I(?)

605
00:40:36,280 --> 00:40:37,520
Hmm!

606
00:40:37,600 --> 00:40:39,760
Now we go help the Doctor.

607
00:40:41,280 --> 00:40:43,360
Rightio.

608
00:40:43,760 --> 00:40:46,480
(SCREAMING)

609
00:40:53,560 --> 00:40:55,120
(BELL TOLLS)

610
00:41:04,880 --> 00:41:06,360
Open the gates!

611
00:41:15,520 --> 00:41:18,200
MAN: It's the Almighty! Look at the sky!

612
00:41:21,840 --> 00:41:23,480
Get out! I need to stabilise the storm.

613
00:41:23,560 --> 00:41:25,840
- We're not leaving you.
- Right,

614
00:41:25,920 --> 00:41:29,200
so one minute it's all, "You make
people a danger to themselves,"

615
00:41:29,280 --> 00:41:31,440
the next it's, "We're not leaving you!"

616
00:41:31,520 --> 00:41:34,560
But if one of you gets squashed
or blown up or eaten, who gets...

617
00:41:34,640 --> 00:41:37,600
(THEY SCREAM)

618
00:41:40,040 --> 00:41:42,840
- What was that?
- Nothing. Bit of an earthquake.

619
00:41:42,920 --> 00:41:45,160
- An earthquake?
- Manipulate the elements,

620
00:41:45,240 --> 00:41:47,000
it can trigger earthquakes,
but don't worry about them.

621
00:41:47,080 --> 00:41:48,280
- No?
- No.

622
00:41:48,360 --> 00:41:50,600
Worry about the tidal waves
caused by the earthquake.

623
00:41:52,360 --> 00:41:56,480
Right, Rosanna's throne is the control hub
but she's locked the program,

624
00:41:56,560 --> 00:41:59,720
so tear out every single wire
and circuit in the throne. Go crazy.

625
00:41:59,800 --> 00:42:01,240
Hit it with a stick, anything.

626
00:42:01,280 --> 00:42:05,320
We need it to shut down
and re-route control to the secondary hub,

627
00:42:05,400 --> 00:42:07,920
which I'm guessing
will also be the generator.

628
00:42:12,040 --> 00:42:14,720
(BEEPING)

629
00:42:16,240 --> 00:42:17,760
(ELECTRONIC WHIRRING)

630
00:42:17,840 --> 00:42:19,640
(BELL TOLLING LOUDLY)

631
00:42:25,720 --> 00:42:27,720
(HE GROANS)

632
00:42:35,040 --> 00:42:37,760
Shut up! Shut up.

633
00:42:37,840 --> 00:42:39,280
That's better!

634
00:42:53,400 --> 00:42:54,880
Oh!

635
00:42:54,960 --> 00:42:56,560
Argh!

636
00:42:56,640 --> 00:42:57,800
I'm OK.

637
00:43:02,240 --> 00:43:04,760
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

638
00:43:04,840 --> 00:43:05,920
There he is!

639
00:43:16,640 --> 00:43:18,400
Come on!

640
00:43:26,360 --> 00:43:28,280
- Come on!
- Come on!

641
00:43:42,120 --> 00:43:44,800
(BIRDSONG)

642
00:43:59,480 --> 00:44:02,480
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

643
00:44:02,560 --> 00:44:04,240
RORY: You did it!

644
00:44:09,880 --> 00:44:11,680
(WHIRRING AND BEEPING)

645
00:44:14,480 --> 00:44:17,600
(CONTINUOUS TONE)

646
00:44:17,680 --> 00:44:19,280
(TONE STOPS)

647
00:44:41,000 --> 00:44:42,800
Rosanna!

648
00:44:42,880 --> 00:44:46,480
One city to save an entire species.

649
00:44:47,640 --> 00:44:50,280
Was that so much to ask?

650
00:44:50,360 --> 00:44:53,440
I told you,
you can't go back and change time.

651
00:44:53,520 --> 00:44:57,400
You mourn, but you live.

652
00:44:57,480 --> 00:44:59,560
I know, Rosanna, I did it.

653
00:45:01,480 --> 00:45:03,440
Tell me, Doctor...

654
00:45:05,000 --> 00:45:08,120
...Can your conscience carry
the weight of another dead race?

655
00:45:09,600 --> 00:45:11,880
Remember us.

656
00:45:14,920 --> 00:45:16,840
Dream of us.

657
00:45:19,360 --> 00:45:20,800
No...

658
00:45:20,880 --> 00:45:22,200
No!

659
00:45:45,720 --> 00:45:48,720
Now, then? What about you two, eh?

660
00:45:48,800 --> 00:45:51,520
Next stop Leadworth Registry Office?

661
00:45:51,600 --> 00:45:54,160
Maybe I can give you away.

662
00:45:56,680 --> 00:45:58,480
It's fine.

663
00:45:58,560 --> 00:46:01,960
Drop me back where you found me.
I'IL just say you've...

664
00:46:02,040 --> 00:46:03,240
Stay.

665
00:46:03,320 --> 00:46:05,360
With us. Please.

666
00:46:05,440 --> 00:46:07,160
Just for a bit.

667
00:46:07,240 --> 00:46:09,520
I want you to stay.

668
00:46:09,600 --> 00:46:11,720
Fine with me.

669
00:46:11,800 --> 00:46:13,200
Yeah?

670
00:46:13,280 --> 00:46:16,080
Yes, I would like that.

671
00:46:16,160 --> 00:46:19,640
Nice one. I will pop the kettle on.

672
00:46:19,720 --> 00:46:21,880
Hey, look at this.

673
00:46:21,960 --> 00:46:24,480
Got my spaceship, got my boys.

674
00:46:24,560 --> 00:46:26,080
My work here is done.

675
00:46:27,760 --> 00:46:30,560
We are not her boys.

676
00:46:30,640 --> 00:46:32,120
- Yeah, we are.
- Yeah, we are.

677
00:46:34,720 --> 00:46:36,360
Rory, listen to that.

678
00:46:36,440 --> 00:46:38,280
Er...what?

679
00:46:38,360 --> 00:46:40,120
All I can hear is...

680
00:46:40,200 --> 00:46:41,440
silence.

681
00:46:44,800 --> 00:46:46,760
ROSANNA: There were cracks.

682
00:46:46,840 --> 00:46:50,640
Through some we saw silence
and the end of all things.

